reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not just for shoes
reviews.reviewText: Now putting it together was a little challenging but got it done and it’s very sturdy , my husband was sceptical, because it didn’t use screws to put together lol ! I ordered it to put my drinks that don’t fit in fridge on , instead of my floor still in plastic !! It looks so much neater , putting my drinks on it 🥰

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Don't expect quality, but for the price it's fine
reviews.reviewText: Behold the masterpiece of budget brilliance! Sure, it might be described as "cheap Chinese junk," but hey, it's so cheap that even your piggy bank is impressed. Assembling it is easier than making a peanut butter sandwich.Is it stylish? it's a statement – a statement that says, "I value budget over boujee." High quality? Let's just say it makes IKEA furniture look like its actually manufactured in Sweden.Perfect for the college kid who's planning to throw it in the dumpster after a year or two. It's practically the Meryl Streep of basic furniture – does the job without demanding an Oscar. Plus, think of it as a short-term relationship; landfills need love too, right? Planet Earth secretly loves being buried under layers of not-so-chic but totally functional treasures. Who wouldn't want that kind of attention?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Cheaper, Smaller, & Flimsier Then Expected
reviews.reviewText: Not at all what I expected. Much smaller, cheaply made, and super flimsy. The price is extortionate considering this should only be about $5.00. In the picture I added, you'll see a small pair of womens hiking boots on this shoe rack and how tiny the rack is in comparison. I also didn't add 2 of the layers because it made each shelf so tiny that my shoes wouldn't fit. Super disappointed not not even worth the hassle of the return.
